## Development Process

This project follows the [ai-dev-blueprint](https://github.com/kaza/ai-dev-blueprint). All principles and playbooks apply:

- **Baseline:** KISS, YAGNI, TDD, spec-anchored (see `philosophy.md`, `spec-anchored.md` in the blueprint)
- **Triple AI review is STRICTLY MANDATORY** for every PR: Gemini + Codex + CodeRabbit. See `how-to-review-code.md`.
- **Regression prevention:** every review finding that results in a code fix MUST have a corresponding automated test that would have caught it.

### Project-specific overrides

This section documents where **this project deviates from the blueprint**. Leave empty if no deviations. Real examples of what goes here:

- **Fast track:** Disabled — all PRs go through full triple review (Gemini + Codex + CodeRabbit). Reason: production cutover stakes; one bad merge is a revenue incident.
- **Extra reviewer:** Security review (`/security-review`) is mandatory for any change to auth, session, or token-handling code.
- **Spec location:** Specs live in `docs/specs/` rather than `specs/` (pre-existing convention in this repo).
- **Test threshold:** Unit-test coverage floor is 90% (raised from blueprint default of no threshold) due to regulated-system requirements.
- **Experiments:** Disabled — this project is production-only; any exploration happens in a separate `<project>-experiments` repo.
- **Fast-track single reviewer:** CodeRabbit only (Codex unavailable here due to repo-size limits).

If there are no deviations, write: "No overrides — blueprint defaults apply as-is."

